<topic xml:id="task-creating-users-cockpit"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <title>Creating user accounts using &cockpit;</title>
  <info>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="jsindelarova@suse.com"/>
  </info>
  <para>
    To add a new user to the system, proceed as follows:
  </para>
  <procedure>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click the <guimenu>Accounts</guimenu> page.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Create new account</guimenu> to open the window that enables
    you to add a new user.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Fill in the user account details.
      </para>
      </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click <guimenu>Create</guimenu> to confirm the account.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        To assign the <guimenu>sudo</guimenu> privileges, or add an SSH key to the account, you need to modify the account as described in <xref linkend="task-modifying-user-accounts"/>.  
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
